.TH new-char
.SH NAME
new-char - server response with IDs and serial values of new characters for the client to control.
.SH DESCRIPTION
The new-char response is sent by the server to inform client about new characters that he now controls.
.br
Is send as a response on successful new-char request.
.br
The new-char request contains a list of IDs and serial values of game module character's.
.br
This ID and serial value can be used by the client to retrieve controlled characters from the module
on the client-side.
.SH JSON EXAMPLE
.nf
{
  "new-char": [
    {
      "id": "char1",
      "serial": "0",
      "name": "charName",
      "ai": true,
      "level": 2,
      "sex": "",
      "race": "",
      "attitude": "",
      "guild": "",
      "alignment": "",
      "pos-x": 0,
      "pos-y": 0,
      "def-pos-x": 0,
      "def-pos-y": 0,
      "hp": 300,
      "mana": 20,
      "exp": 1000,
      "resore": true,
      "attributes": {
        "str": 0,
        "con": 0,
        "dex": 0,
        "int": 0,
        "wis": 0
      },
      "inventory": {
        "cap": 10,
        "items": null
      },
      "equipment": {
        "items": null
      },
      "quests": {
        "quests": null
      },
      "crafting": {
        "recipes": null
      },
      "trainings": {
        "AttrTrainings": null
      },
      "flags": null,
      "effects": null,
      "skills": null,
      "memory": null,
      "dialogs": null
    }
  ]
}
